[Although vaccination was ordered, it must be of the correct strain to be
protective. Furthermore, vaccination does not provide immediate protection,
there must be time to mount an immune response. Generally, this considered
to be about 2 weeks. Chen's animals may not have had time to form an
immunological response, may have been incubating the disease at the time of
inoculation, or the strain of vaccine may have been incorrect for the stain
of outbreak. - MOD.TG
